],"paidOnly":false,"problem":"You have a graph of `n` nodes labeled from `0` to `n - 1`. You are given an integer n and a list of `edges` where `edges[i] = [ai, bi]` indicates that there is an undirected edge between nodes `ai` and `bi` in the graph.\n\nReturn `true` *if the edges of the given graph make up a valid tree, and* `false` *otherwise*.\n\n**Example 1:**\n\n[[img:leetcode_seed/assets/problems/0261-graph-valid-tree/261-tree1-graph.jpg]]\n\nInput: n = 5, edges = [[0,1],[0,2],[0,3],[1,4]]\nOutput: true\n\n**Example 2:**\n\n[[img:leetcode_seed/assets/problems/0261-graph-valid-tree/261-tree2-graph.jpg]]\n\nInput: n = 5, edges = [[0,1],[1,2],[2,3],[1,3],[1,4]]\nOutput: false\n\n**Constraints:**\n\n- `1 <= n <= 2000`\n\n- `0 <= edges.length <= 5000`\n\n- `edges[i].length == 2`\n\n- `0 <= ai, bi < n`\n\n- `ai != bi`\n\n- There are no self-loops or repeated edges.","problemLink":"https://leetcode.com/problems/graph-valid-tree/","problemName":"Graph Valid Tree","problemNumber":261,"problemSlug":"graph-valid-tree","schemaVersion":2,"sequenceIndex":261,"solutionApproaches":[]},{"assets":[],"categories":["Database"],"constraintBlocks":[],"contentBlocks":[{"sequence":0,"text":"Table: `Trips`","type":"text"},{"sequence":1,"text":"+-------------+----------+\n| Column Name | Type     |\n+-------------+----------+\n| id          | int      |\n| client_id   | int      |\n| driver_id   | int      |\n| city_id     | int      |\n| status      | enum     |\n| request_at  | varchar  |     \n+-------------+----------+\nid is the primary key (column with unique values) for this table.\nThe table holds all taxi trips. Each trip has a unique id, while client_id and driver_id are foreign keys to the users_id at the Users table.\nStatus is an ENUM (category) type of ('completed', 'cancelled_by_driver', 'cancelled_by_client').","type":"code"},{"sequence":2,"text":"Table: `Users`","type":"text"},{"sequence":3,"text":"+-------------+----------+\n| Column Name | Type     |\n+-------------+